cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.DS 

This paper discusses information-centric networks, which are a type of network architecture for distributing content on the Internet. The paper specifically focuses on caching performance metrics in these networks. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses security issues, which could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses caching algorithms and network topology, which could place it in the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes new metrics and discusses the need for a systematic understanding of caching metrics, which could place it in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
